<h2 class="bold font-l">North's Workshop</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
North's Workshop is a gigantic Russian Palace located in North Pole. It has a huge workshop were the Yetis and North work and design toys for the children of the world and huge room where the Globe of the World is located. It may also have multiple room for the Yetis, Elves, and the reindeer to stay and sleep. It also has an office were North makes his toy design from ice. And a base where the sleigh is keep with the reindeer. The workshop acts as a meeting HQ for the Guardians whenever they are needed, having a tough enough security that Jack Frost has tried and failed to infiltrate. </p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="fv0ljf" data-video-descrip="Christmas Town is second holiday realm featured (the only other one seen being Halloween Town) in The Nightmare Before Christmas. It is portrayed as a bright and colorful town covered in snow and populated by elves. The area includes in-door toy factories where elves work, Santa Claus's home, living spaces where the elves live, a carousel, bakeries and a train. The protagonist Jack Skellington accidentally happens upon this world when he finds the Hinterlands outside the borders of Halloween Town and finds a door shaped like a Christmas tree where he is literally pulled into it. It is likely that Christmas Town has its own set of doors, as Jack, Lock, Shock and Barrel where able to return to Halloween Town with no trouble." data-video-title="Christmas Town" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/fv0ljf_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/fv0ljf.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/ChristmasTown" data-video-tropename="Christmas Town" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="WesternAnimation/TheNightmareBeforeChristmas" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/fv0ljf.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">Christmas Town</span></p>
</a>
