<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="riud2j" data-vimeo-id="467512623" data-video-descrip="North's Workshop is a gigantic Russian Palace located in North Pole. It has a huge workshop were the Yetis and North work and design toys for the children of the world and huge room where the Globe of the World is located. It may also have multiple room for the Yetis, Elves, and the reindeer to stay and sleep. It also has an office were North makes his toy design from ice. And a base where the sleigh is keep with the reindeer. The workshop acts as a meeting HQ for the Guardians whenever they are needed, having a tough enough security that Jack Frost has tried and failed to infiltrate." data-video-title="North's Workshop" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/riud2j_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/rise_of_the_guardians_2764_8.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/ChristmasTown" data-video-tropename="Christmas Town" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="5.00" data-video-rating-count="5" data-video-media-sources="WesternAnimation/RiseOfTheGuardians" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/rise_of_the_guardians_2764_8.jpg">
